            <h3 style="margin-left: 8px;">Tomato Basil Bruschetta:</h3>
            <p>
              Description:  A classic Italian appetizer that features fresh tomatoes, basil, garlic, and crusty bread. It's bursting with flavors and perfect for summer gatherings.
              Ingredients: 4 ripe tomatoes(diced),1/4 cup fresh basil leaves, chopped 2 cloves garlic, minced2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil,Salt and pepper to taste, Baguette or crusty bread slices
              Instructions:
              In a bowl, combine the diced tomatoes, chopped basil, minced garlic, olive oil, salt, and pepper.
              Stir everything together until well mixed.
              Let the mixture sit at room temperature for about 15-20 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.
              Meanwhile, preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).
              Slice the baguette or crusty bread into 1/2-inch thick slices.
              Place the bread slices on a baking sheet and bake for about 8-10 minutes until they are crispy and lightly toasted.
              Remove the bread from the oven and let it cool slightly.
              Once the bread has cooled, spoon the tomato basil mixture generously over each slice.
              Serve immediately and enjoy the vibrant flavors of this delicious bruschetta.
            </p>
          </div>
