            <h3 style="margin-left: 8px;"> Fried Frog Legs:</h3>
            <p>
              Description: A classic preparation that results in crispy and flavorful frog legs.
              Ingredients:8 pairs of frog legs, 1 cup all-purpose flour, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon black pepper, 1/2 teaspoon paprika, Vegetable oil for frying, Lemon wedges(optional)
              Instructions:
              Rinse the frog legs under cold water and pat them dry with paper towels.
              In a shallow dish, mix the flour, salt, black pepper, and paprika together.
              Heat vegetable oil in a deep skillet or frying pan over medium-high heat.
              Dredge each frog leg in the flour mixture, shaking off any excess.
              Carefully place the frog legs in the hot oil and cook for about 4-5 minutes on each side, or until they turn golden brown and crispy.
              Remove the frog legs from the oil and transfer them to a paper towel-lined plate to drain excess oil.
              Serve the fried frog legs hot with lemon wedges on the side, if desired.
            </p>
